
                        Section 2 - Notes
                        VOLUME Instruction

1.  Dockerfile in this directory.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    # Dockerfile for VOLUME instruction
    FROM alpine
    RUN mkdir /myvol
    RUN echo "this is some text" > /myvol/data
    VOLUME /myvol
    CMD ["/bin/sh"]

2.  Build image.

    $ docker build -t vol .

3.  Run container and show data in /mvol.

    $ docker run -it vol
    / # cat /myvol/data
    this is some text
    / # exit

4. Show volume.

   $ docker volume ls
   DRIVER              VOLUME NAME
   local               a2d19de6460...
  
5. Inspect volume.

   $ docker volume inspect a2d19de6460...
   [
    {
        "CreatedAt": "2019-09-20T09:13:22Z",
        "Driver": "local",
        "Labels": null,
        "Mountpoint": "/var/lib/docker/volumes/
             a2d19de6460.../_data",
        "Name": "a2d19de6460...",
        "Options": null,
        "Scope": "local"
    }
   ]

6. Cleanup

   $ docker container prune -f ; docker volume prune -f
